To understand the _universality_ of _pan-roasting_, let's cook some _vegetables_ this way.

Like a lot of people, I _grew up_ on _boiled-to-death_ Brussels sprouts and I _did not like_ them. In the last generation, _chefs_ have made this vegetable _popular_ again. But while the _combinations_ of _Brussels sprouts_ with _bacon_ and _kimchi_ helped turn them trendy, it was the _cooking method_ that _sold_ them.

_Instead_ of _boiling_ the "Barbie cabbages" _whole_, chefs started _cutting_ them in _half_, using the _cut side surface_ to create a _bounty of flavour_ and _colour_. Now that you know how to _pan-roast_ a chicken breast, you probably know what to do.

